199. quid. ais Ρ a common phrase in Terence; used,

(1) as a request for information, usually when a remark has not been heard or understood, as here. Cf. 833.

(2) as an exclamation of surprise or anger at some remark which seems scarcely credible, e. g. 755, 873, 1040.

(3) to introduce a new point in conversation, or to call attention, like dis donc. ‘ What do you say to this? ’ ‘look here.‘ Cf. 798 note.
